<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Help - Huququlator</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Navigation Bar -->
    <nav class="navbar">
        <% if (loggedIn) { %>
            <span>Welcome, <%= username %></span>
            <div class="navbar-right">
                <a href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a>
                <a href="/upload">Upload Transactions</a>
                <a href="/filter-rules">Categorization rules</a>
                <a href="/transactions">View Transactions</a>
                <a href="/logout">Log out</a>
            </div>
        <% } else { %>
            <div class="navbar-right">
                <a href="/login">Login</a>
                <a href="/register">Register</a>
            </div>
        <% } %>
    </nav>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="main-content">
        <h1>Help and Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p>Below are answers to common questions and explanations for each section of the calculator.</p>

        <div class="faq-section">
            <!-- Question 1 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h2>What is "Excess wealth for the year"?</h2>
                <p>Placeholder explanation: This field represents the total income and assets subject to Huququllah for the year.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 2 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h2>What are "Unnecessary expenditures"?</h2>
                <p>Placeholder explanation: This field includes expenditures that can be added back to calculate your total excess wealth.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 3 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h2>What does "Wealth Huquq previously paid on" mean?</h2>
                <p>Placeholder explanation: This refers to wealth that you have already paid Huququllah on, which is excluded from the current calculation.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 4 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h2>How is "Today's value of 19 Mithqals of gold" calculated?</h2>
                <p>Placeholder explanation: The calculator uses the current market price of gold to determine the value of 19 Mithqals (equivalent to 2.225 troy ounces).</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Question 5 -->
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h2>Why is Huququllah calculated as 19%?</h2>
                <p>Placeholder explanation: Huququllah is a 19% payment on the wealth specified above, as outlined in the Bahá'í laws.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
